OL,6,F"Anne has chosen to die," they wrote.
OL,7,F"She died gently and not alone. I hope
OL,8,Fher letters help you to accept this.
OL,9,FAll official papers and her urn will
OL,10,Fbe sent to her brother John."
OL,12,FHorrified, Delia replied, "This was
OL,13,FNOT the right decision for her".
OL,15,FBut Pegasos insisted in its emails to
OL,16,Fthe family, "Anne no longer wanted to
OL,17,Flive, she felt alone and superfluous.
OL,18,FShe also did not want to grow old.
OL,19,FThis is a free decision of a free
OL,20,Fperson."
